neral performance. Many companies have nevertheless broken those costs out i=
n their unaudited press releases.=20
Many more are likely to do so in the fourth quarter. Indeed, 2001 is shaping=
 up to be one for the record books. A poor economy and the devastating after=
effects of September 11 have resulted in a slew of unusual charges that are =
unlikely to recur and that no one could have foreseen. But there's a growing=
